neuro
------------------------------------------
libneuro is an abstraction layer for applications, it is actually a toolkit
that implements a lot of kits that should be vital for (at least) games. The
initial use of libneuro was to provide a method to have multi layered (order by
which images are drawn on screen) drawing which I call : the painter's
algorithm. By then, it started including various other functionality like
events handling, abstraction of low libraries (libneuro used to use strictly
SDL), arguments parsing to support the input of console arguments(to implement
incredibly easy argument processing on those console applications in a similar
way as all those POSIX console applications do, i.e : someapp --help), etc.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.0-0.212.g6af8fea4bbad
  libSDL1.2_0-1.2.15-3
  libfreetype6-2.13.3-1
  libneuro-devel-0.49.42+git20150618-1bl1
  libneuro0-0.49.42+git20150618-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.3.0-1
  zlib0-1.3.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20240607-1
  binutils-2.43.1-1
  cygport-0.36.9-1
  gcc-core-12.4.0-3
  libSDL-devel-1.2.15-3
  libfreetype-devel-2.13.3-1
  libtool-2.5.3-1
  make-4.4.1-2
  zlib-devel-1.3.1-1

Canonical website:
  https://repo.or.cz/w/neuro.git

Canonical download:
  https://repo.or.cz/neuro.git

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack neuro-0.49.42+git20150618-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./neuro-0.49.42+git20150618-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/neuro-0.49.42+git20150618-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/neuro-0.49.42+git20150618-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libneuro0-0.49.42+git20150618-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libneuro-devel-0.49.42+git20150618-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

